Install & open Power BI Desktop (free from Microsoft).

Home → Get data → Excel → choose your .xlsx file.

In Navigator choose the Table or Sheet(s) you need. Click Transform Data to open Power Query if you need to clean (recommended) or Load to import as‑is.

In Power Query: set proper data types, remove unnecessary rows, rename columns. Click Close & Apply.

After load, switch to Report view (left pane). Your tables/columns appear in the Fields pane.
